1. ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW
================================================================================

CONCEPT
-------
A single agent handles 88 service request types. Service definitions, field
schemas, and conditional rules all live in Dataverse. Adaptive cards for the
Form path are pre-built and cached on the Service record, rebuilt automatically
when definitions change. Quick Chat uses a Generative Answers loop grounded by
a per-service schema document in SharePoint. Adding a new service requires only
a data operation and a schema file upload â€” no topic changes.

FLOW SUMMARY
------------
  User opens agent
    â””â”€ Conversational Start
         â”œâ”€ PA: Get Service List â†’ Service picker card
         â””â”€ Mode picker card (Quick Chat / Form)
              â”œâ”€ Quick Chat Topic
              â”‚    â”œâ”€ Generative Answers loop (SharePoint schema knowledge)
              â”‚    â”œâ”€ Completion detection (JSON with "complete": true)
              â”‚    â””â”€ PA: Submit Request â†’ Dataverse
              â””â”€ Form Topic
                   â”œâ”€ Read sbs_cardjson from sbs_Service record
                   â”œâ”€ Render pre-built adaptive card
                   â””â”€ PA: Submit Request â†’ Dataverse

CARD LIFECYCLE
--------------
  sbs_ServiceField / sbs_Field row changed
    â””â”€ Trigger flow sets sbs_cardbuildstatus = "Pending"
  
  Nightly scheduled flow (e.g. 11 PM)
    â””â”€ Queries all Pending service records
         â””â”€ Calls SRA - Card Builder child flow per service
              â””â”€ Writes built card JSON back to sbs_Service
                   â””â”€ Sets status to Built or Failed

  Override path:
    If sbs_cardoverridejson is populated on sbs_Service,
    Card Builder returns it directly without generating.

